commit.message:
adifmerg allow RST_RCVD and RST_SENT to be "0" for 0 dB signal reports

The validity of QSO record is tested in TestRecValid() subroutine. Integer
zero is also False in Perl and previously signal report "0" was not printed.

For text inputs shorthand notation "+0" could be used too.

adifmerg add 'ncnty' and 'nstate' queries

These queries '-q ncnty' or '-q nstate' print total number of counties or
states for all dxcc entities in the ADIF log file.

adifmerg add printing of county and state statistics with option -i

Total number of counties and states for all DXCC entities is printed.

With option -v list of counties and states is printed for each DXCC entity.

The county is also known as Secondary Administrative Subdivision in
adif.org and state as Primary Administrative Subdivision.

EQSL_QSL_RCVD and LOTW_QSL_RCVD flags 'Y' are now counted as confirmed
QSOs when printing number of DXCCs.

Update adifmerg and qsorep manual pages

Reference to new queries 'npota', 'nwwff', 'pota' and 'wwff' was added.

Brief description of 'file check dxcc [errors]' in qsorep manual page.

qsorep check QSO DXCC with option -c in adifmerg

The command 'file check dxcc [errors]' should be used only with local copy
of /usr/share/dxcc/cty.plist and not by calling 'dxcc'.

The printed errors need to be checked against received QSO confirmation which
could be a paper QSL card or record in the Logbook of the World. The file
'cty.plist' does not know where the contacted station was located when the
two way radio contact was made.

adifmerg add check of DXCC and MY_DXCC entity codes

The value in fields DXCC and MY_DXCC is compared to data in %ctylist hash
for given call sign. This is done if DXCC or MY_DXCC is non-zero and
non-empty. If value from %ctylist is different from DXCC or MY_DXCC, error
'dxcc?' or 'mydxcc?' is printed.

adifmerg touch QSO merging code

Should not print error any more when one of the records is empty.

runtest add example of received paper QSL cards

The typed text file qsl_paper.txt is converted to ADIF-format and sorted to
ascending time order.

adifmerg print POTA_REF and WWFF_REF with -l -v options

This is verbosed printing of QSO record data.

adifmerg very basic test to see if CSV-file has header line

Only first two items on first line of CSV-file are tested.

adifmerg add POTA and WWFF statistics

The number of POTA references is give with query '-q npota' and list is these is printed with '-q pota'.

Number of WWFF references is given by query '-q nwwff' and list is printed with '-q wwff'.

adifmerg add testing of valid WWFF reference

The WWFF reference is matched to pattern xxFF-nnnn described https://www.adif.org/ .

adifmerg add testing of valid POTA reference

The POTA reference is matched to string xxxx-nnnnn[@yyyyyy] withtout reference to actual list of valid Parks on the
Air references. For example 'OH-01510'.

adifmerg update QSO fields and modes to ADIF 3.1.4

Add new fields for (MY_)ALTITUDE, GRIDSQUARE_EXT, HAMLOG, HAMQTH, POTA_REF, REGION and WWFF_REF.

Update modes from https://www.adif.org/

adifmerg update list of valid SOTA references

These are from https://www.sotadata.org.uk/en/

adifmerg check record name with options -A, -D, -S, -F and -R

Warning is printed if record name is unknown with option -D. In other cases program exits with error.

Add instructions on cty.plist file to adifmerg manual page

This data from AD1C is used to check validity of country, CQ zone and ITU zone for the call sign.

adifmerg add support for ancillary post fixes in call sign check

The following patterns are not matched to cty.plist data hash: /P, /M, /MM,
/AM and /A. These cases need manual editing. But VE7xxx/W7 should map to
correct country now when option '-c' is used.

adifmerg clean up call sign check code with cty.plist hash

Map cty.plist country names 'Fed. Rep. of Germany' and 'Dem. Rep. of Congo'
to full names.

adifmerg use local cty.plist file to check call sign if available

The file path is set by $ctyplist variable. Data is filled into hash %ctylist
and should be faster than calling 'dxcc'.

Only ancillary prefixes like F/OH7BF/P are handeled correctly while postfixes
like VE7xxx/W7 are not.

Some sanity check is needed when using the option '-c' as the results may be
incorrect.

adifmerg add leading zero to three digit time in CSV-file

The adif-files require leading zero in hour, minute and second specifier.

https://adif.org/314/ADIF_314.htm#Data_Types

Update valid QSO year to range 1930 - 2023

Thanks to DL4AN for spotting this.

Allow dot in abbreviated dxcc country names with option -c

As an example the 'dxcc German-call-sign' returns

Country Name:   Fed. Rep. of Germany

Fix handling the dxcc program output in CheckQso()

commit.message:
fix: refactor CheckQso() using line split

* This fix depends on the line positional output of DJ1YFK's
  dxcc program
* The author of this fix thinks that
  this code makes much more sense than parsing the whole
  output including the newlines...
fix: add opt_c regex fix

fix: handle Country Names correctly for calling dxcc subprogram

* cty.dat contains up to five words for the Country Names
* Current implementation only picks up the first two words of the
  Country Names, which fails in many cases such as "Republic of Korea"
  and "US Virgin Islands"
* This patch handles up to five words for the Country Name output of
  DJ1YFK's DXCC program

adifmerg clean up code

Add space and replace tabs with four space characters to make code easier to
read. Hopefully nothing was broken.

adifmerg update SOTA association codes in CheckSota subroutine

Only association code is checked without verification of region code and valid
summit reference.

adifmerg clean up CSV hash handling code

Replace tabs with space and add space to make code more easy to read.
